---

---

<section class="w-full min-h-[60vh] flex flex-col justify-center px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16 py-section">
  <div class="max-w-prose">
    <p class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-muted mb-6 tracking-wide">
      aiconsole <span class="text-accent">●</span> local-first AI governance
    </p>

    <h1
      class="font-display font-bold text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl leading-tight tracking-tight mb-6"
    >
      Every prompt you send<br />
      <span class="text-accent">ships your codebase.</span>
    </h1>

    <p class="text-xl text-ink-muted mb-4 max-w-narrow">
      aiconsole intercepts prompts at the OS level — before they hit the network. Redact secrets,
      block leaks, and keep a tamper-evident log. No SDK. No cloud. Nothing leaves your machine
      unless you say so.
    </p>

    <p class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-subtle mb-10 max-w-narrow">
      Works with Claude Code · Cursor · Copilot · Ollama · GPT · Gemini
    </p>

    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-4 mb-12">
      <a
        href="#waitlist"
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center bg-accent text-surface font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-md hover:bg-accent-hover active:bg-accent-press transition-colors"
      >
        Join the waitlist →
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/OpsKern/aiconsole-core"
        class="text-ink-muted hover:text-ink text-sm transition-colors"
      >
        View the code on GitHub ↗
      </a>
    </div>

    <figure class="mt-8" aria-label="Example aiconsole intercept output">
      <div
        class="rounded-lg bg-surface-raised border border-ink-subtle/20 overflow-hidden font-mono text-xs leading-relaxed"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Terminal output showing aiconsole blocking a prompt that contained .env secrets"
      >
        <div
          class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 border-b border-ink-subtle/20 bg-surface-sunken"
        >
          <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-red-500/60"></span>
          <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-yellow-500/60"></span>
          <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-green-500/60"></span>
          <span class="ml-2 text-ink-subtle text-[10px] tracking-wide">terminal</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 space-y-1 text-[11px] sm:text-xs">
          <p class="text-ink-subtle">$ claude code --write-code auth-middleware.go</p>
          <p class="text-ink-muted">
            <span class="text-accent font-semibold">[aiconsole]</span> intercepted outbound → api.anthropic.com
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-muted pl-4">
            <span class="text-red-400">✗</span> .env:3 &nbsp;&nbsp;
            <span class="text-ink-subtle">AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY</span>=<span class="text-red-400/80"
              >AKIA···</span
            >
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-muted pl-4">
            <span class="text-red-400">✗</span> .env:7 &nbsp;&nbsp;
            <span class="text-ink-subtle">DATABASE_URL</span>=<span class="text-red-400/80"
              >postgres://prod:···</span
            >
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-muted pl-4">
            <span class="text-red-400">✗</span> src/config.go:14 &nbsp;
            <span class="text-ink-subtle">STRIPE_SECRET</span>=<span class="text-red-400/80"
              >sk_live_···</span
            >
          </p>
          <p class="text-accent/80 font-semibold">
            &nbsp;&nbsp;→ BLOCKED &nbsp;policy: no-secrets &nbsp;ref: a3c2f9
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-subtle">
            prompt not sent &nbsp;·&nbsp; logged to ~/.aiconsole/audit.log
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <figcaption class="sr-only">
        aiconsole intercepts the outbound prompt, finds three secrets in context (.env and config
        file), blocks the send, and writes a tamper-evident entry to the local audit log.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>
</section>
